description: Campsite - Primitive - Non Reservable - Fee. Large camp on river left with a lower-bench landing; camping is available on the upper bench closer to the trail.

name: Mouth of Dominguez
description: Campsite - Primitive - Non Reservable - Fee. Large camp on river left at the mouth of Domiguez Creek. Hikers from Bridgeport and other boaters park and walk directly through this camp to access Big Domiguez canyon.

name: Poverty Flats
description: Campsite - Primitive - Non Reservable - Fee. Camp on river left; steep bank leads to well-shaded large camp with access to desert canyon hikes.

name: Red Wall
description: Campsite - Primitive - Non Reservable - Fee. Medium-sized camp on river left below rock wall and shaded alcoves; small tamarisk landing.

name: Kelso Draw
description: Campsite - Primitive - Non Reservable - Fee. Large camp on river left marked by large cottonwood tree. Flat, willow-heavy landing; camp is also accessible by UTV.

name: Tunnel Point
description: Campsite - Primitive - Non Reservable - Fee. Camp on river right with swift entry; only camp without train noise. Access to historic tunnel construction material out of the back of camp.

name: Riverside
description: Campsite - Primitive - Non Reservable - Fee. Small camp on river left with a small landing; access to trail.

name: Leonard's Beach
description: Campsite - Primitive - Non Reservable - Fee. A small, sunny, low-water camp on river left. Good winter camp.

name: Powerline
description: Campsite - Primitive - Non Reservable - Fee. Large camp on river right with abundant shade. Camp has a small bank to step up at most flows; look for eagles perched on opposite canyon walls.

name: Swallowtail
description: Campsite - Primitive - Non Reservable - Fee. Brushy flat bench on river left, with abundant train ambiance.

name: Leonard's Basin
description: Campsite - Primitive - Non Reservable - Fee. Large grassy landing on river left with shade. Good access to Leonard’s Basin for hiking; please practice leave no trace principles as you expore.

name: Lower Cottonwood
description: Campsite - Primitive - Non Reservable - Fee. Large camp on river left with brushy landing and camping on both sides of the trail. This is the last camp in the Domiguez zone.

name: Echo Wall
description: Campsite - Primitive - Non Reservable - Fee. Large camp on river left with cottonwood trees, and opposite of sandstone wall. Good access to sand wash.

name: Sage Flats
description: Campsite - Primitive - Non Reservable - Fee. Small willowy landing on river left opens to large cottonwood-shaded camp. Popular with commercial groups.

name: Sheep Factory
description: Campsite - Primitive - Non Reservable - Fee. Large camp on river left with shade, large grassy landing. Abundant hookless cactus on the hillside above camp, local threatened species. Last designated camp in the stretch.
